   10. Healthcare Liability Disclaimer.

       IN ADDITION TO THE DISCLAIMERS IN SECTIONS 7 AND 8 ABOVE:

       (a) HEALTHCARE USE DISCLAIMER. This software is provided for healthcare
           interoperability purposes. The Licensor and Contributors make no
           representations or warranties regarding the software's suitability,
           accuracy, or reliability for clinical decision-making, patient care,
           diagnosis, treatment, or any other healthcare purpose.

       (b) PATIENT SAFETY. You acknowledge that the software may be used in
           connection with Protected Health Information (PHI) and patient care
           systems. You are solely responsible for:
           - Ensuring patient safety in your deployment
           - Validating all data and outputs before clinical use
           - Maintaining appropriate safeguards for PHI
           - Compliance with all applicable healthcare regulations

       (c) NO MEDICAL ADVICE. This software does not provide medical advice,
           diagnosis, or treatment. It is an integration and interoperability
           tool only.

       (d) REGULATORY COMPLIANCE. You are solely responsible for ensuring
           your use of the Work complies with all applicable laws and
           regulations, including but not limited to HIPAA, GDPR, FDA
           regulations, and local healthcare privacy laws.

       (e) MAXIMUM LIABILITY LIMITATION. To the maximum extent permitted by
           applicable law, in no event shall any Contributor be liable for
           any damages whatsoever, including but not limited to medical
           malpractice, patient harm, data breaches, PHI disclosure, or any
           other healthcare-related damages arising from use of this software.

   11. Healthcare and Anti-Commercialization Provisions.

       (a) HEALTHCARE PROVIDER EXEMPTION (FREE USE).
           Healthcare providers may use the Work freely without restriction,
           regardless of organization size, revenue, or number of employees.
           
           "Healthcare Providers" include:
           - Hospitals and health systems (any size)
           - Medical clinics and physician practices
           - Community health centers
           - Public health departments and agencies
           - Academic medical centers and teaching hospitals
           - Long-term care facilities and nursing homes
           - Mental health and behavioral health facilities
           - Rehabilitation and specialty care centers
           - Non-profit healthcare organizations
           - Health research institutions
           
           Healthcare Providers may:
           ✅ Use in production environments freely
           ✅ Deploy at any scale without restriction
           ✅ Modify and customize for their needs
           ✅ Share modifications with other healthcare providers
           ✅ Contribute improvements back to the project

       (b) GENERAL OPEN-SOURCE USE.
           All individuals, small businesses, non-profits, educational
           institutions, and government agencies may use the Work freely
           under standard Apache 2.0 terms without restriction.

       (c) PROHIBITED COMMERCIALIZATION.
           You may NOT use the Work to:
           
           (i)    Sell, resell, or license the Work as a standalone product
           (ii)   Offer the Work as a commercial SaaS platform to third parties
           (iii)  Create proprietary derivative products for commercial sale
           (iv)   Package and distribute the Work for profit without
                  substantial additional value
           (v)    Market competing commercial products based primarily on
                  this Work
           (vi)   Remove attribution and rebrand as your own product for sale

       (d) PERMITTED COMMERCIAL ACTIVITIES.
           You MAY:
           
           (i)    Provide professional services (consulting, implementation,
                  training, support) using the Work
           (ii)   Deploy the Work as part of your internal business operations
           (iii)  Use the Work as a component in a larger value-added solution
           (iv)   Offer managed hosting services with substantial value-add
           (v)    Develop and sell plugins/extensions that add new functionality
           (vi)   Provide integration services connecting the Work to other systems

       (e) SUBSTANTIAL VALUE-ADD REQUIREMENT.
           If You incorporate the Work into a commercial offering, You must
           provide SUBSTANTIAL additional value beyond the Work itself, such as:
           
           (i)    Significant custom features or functionality
           (ii)   Professional services and expertise
           (iii)  Integration with proprietary systems
           (iv)   Managed operations and support services
           (v)    Domain-specific customizations
           
           Simply repackaging or hosting the Work without substantial
           additional value is prohibited.

       (f) ATTRIBUTION AND TRANSPARENCY.
           If You offer commercial services based on the Work:
           
           (i)    Clearly disclose that the core platform is OpenHIMS open-source
           (ii)   Provide attribution to the OpenHIMS project
           (iii)  Do not claim the Work as your proprietary technology
           (iv)   Link to the official OpenHIMS project where possible
           (v)    Distinguish your value-add from the open-source core

       (g) ENFORCEMENT AND VIOLATIONS.
           Violation of anti-commercialization provisions shall:
           
           (i)    Terminate all licenses granted under this License immediately
           (ii)   Require cessation of prohibited commercial activities
           (iii)  May result in legal action for breach of license terms
           (iv)   Require payment of damages and disgorgement of profits
           (v)    May result in public disclosure of violation

       (h) QUESTIONS AND CLARIFICATIONS.
           If You are unsure whether your intended use is permitted:
           
           - Email: legal@openhims.org for guidance
           - Generally: If you're helping healthcare, you're fine
           - Generally: If you're just reselling our work, you're not
           - When in doubt, ask before proceeding

   12. Optional Proprietary Extensions by Licensor.

       IMPORTANT: The OpenHIMS core platform is and will always remain
       completely open-source. This section only addresses optional
       proprietary extensions that the Licensor may develop separately.

       (a) LICENSOR'S RIGHT TO CREATE PROPRIETARY EXTENSIONS.
           While the OpenHIMS core platform remains fully open-source, the
           Licensor reserves the right to develop and distribute certain
           OPTIONAL packages, modules, or features under separate proprietary
           licenses that are NOT subject to this open-source license.
           
           These are completely separate products, not part of the core platform.

       (b) CORE PLATFORM REMAINS FULLY FUNCTIONAL.
           The open-source core platform provides complete, production-ready
           healthcare interoperability functionality without any proprietary
           extensions. Proprietary extensions are OPTIONAL enhancements only.
           
           The Licensor commits to:
           (i)    Never removing features from open-source to create paid versions
           (ii)   Maintaining the core as fully functional and competitive
           (iii)  Never requiring proprietary extensions for standard use cases
           (iv)   Documenting which features are open-source vs. proprietary

       (c) SCOPE OF OPTIONAL PROPRIETARY EXTENSIONS.
           Optional proprietary extensions may include:
           
           (i)    Advanced enterprise management consoles
           (ii)   Specialized analytics and business intelligence
           (iii)  AI/ML predictive models and algorithms
           (iv)   Proprietary optimization algorithms
           (v)    White-label or OEM-specific versions
           (vi)   Managed service automation tools
           
           These are value-added enhancements, not core functionality.

       (d) COMMUNITY CAN BUILD ALTERNATIVES.
           The community is explicitly encouraged and permitted to build
           open-source alternatives to any proprietary extensions. The
           Licensor will:
           
           (i)    Maintain open, documented APIs for all integrations
           (ii)   Never create intentional incompatibilities
           (iii)  Support community-built alternatives
           (iv)   No lock-in mechanisms or proprietary protocols
           (v)    Ensure core platform works with any compatible extensions

       (e) SEPARATE LICENSING FOR PROPRIETARY EXTENSIONS.
           Any proprietary extensions are subject to their own separate:
           
           (i)   End User License Agreement (EULA)
           (ii)  Pricing and licensing terms
           (iii) Support and maintenance agreements
           (iv)  Distribution restrictions
           
           These terms do NOT affect the open-source core platform.

       (f) TRANSPARENCY COMMITMENT.
           The Licensor commits to:
           
           (i)    Clearly label what is open-source vs. proprietary
           (ii)   Publish a list of proprietary extensions (if any)
           (iii)  Never mislead users about open-source status
           (iv)   Respond to community feedback on commercialization
           (v)    Prioritize open-source development over proprietary extensions

       (g) HEALTHCARE PROVIDERS GET FREE ACCESS.
           Healthcare providers (as defined in Section 11.a) receive free
           access to proprietary extensions if available, in support of
           their mission to improve healthcare delivery.

       (h) NOTE ON CURRENT STATUS.
           As of the date of this license, no proprietary extensions exist.
           All OpenHIMS components are fully open-source. This section
           reserves the right for future optional proprietary extensions
           should they be developed.
           
           Any future proprietary extensions will be announced transparently
           to the community.

   13. Audit Rights.

       If You are a Commercial Entity or Healthcare Enterprise using the Work,
       You agree that the Licensor may, upon reasonable notice and during
       normal business hours, audit Your use of the Work to verify compliance
       with these license terms. You agree to reasonably cooperate with such
       audits and provide necessary documentation.

   14. No Confusion or Misrepresentation.

       (a) CLEAR DISTINCTION REQUIRED.
           You must clearly distinguish between:
           
           (i)   Open-source components licensed under this license
           (ii)  Commercial-only packages with proprietary licenses
           (iii) Your own modifications and derivative works
           (iv)  Third-party components and integrations

       (b) ATTRIBUTION AND BRANDING.
           When using both open-source and commercial-only packages:
           
           (i)   Properly attribute the open-source core platform
           (ii)  Do not claim commercial packages are open-source
           (iii) Do not remove or modify license notifications
           (iv)  Follow branding guidelines for OpenHIMS trademarks
           (v)   See BRANDING-GUIDE.md for detailed requirements

