   18. Founder Service Request Program.

       (a) ELIGIBILITY TO REQUEST FREE SERVICES.
           Any organization or individual using the Work may submit a request
           to the project founders for complimentary professional services,
           support, or assistance, regardless of organization size, revenue,
           or commercial status.

       (b) TYPES OF SERVICES AVAILABLE.
           Organizations may request:
           
           (i)    Implementation and deployment assistance
           (ii)   Technical support and troubleshooting
           (iii)  Custom development or integration work
           (iv)   Training and knowledge transfer
           (v)    Architecture and design consultation
           (vi)   Compliance and security guidance
           (vii)  Migration from legacy systems
           (viii) Any other professional services related to OpenHIMS

       (c) REQUEST PROCESS.
           To request free services from founders:
           
           (i)   Submit request via email to: founders@openhims.org
           (ii)  Include organization details and service description
           (iii) Explain use case and community benefit
           (iv)  Describe why funding is not available
           (v)   Specify timeline and scope of assistance needed

       (d) EVALUATION CRITERIA.
           Founders will evaluate requests based on:
           
           (i)   Community and public health benefit
           (ii)  Organization's mission alignment (non-profit, healthcare
                 access, underserved populations, research, education)
           (iii) Technical merit and learning opportunity
           (iv)  Founder availability and capacity
           (v)   Potential to advance the OpenHIMS ecosystem
           (vi)  Financial constraints and genuine need

       (e) RESPONSE AND COMMITMENT.
           - All requests will receive a response within 14 business days
           - Approved requests may receive:
             * Full service delivery at no cost
             * Partial service delivery with discounted commercial rate
             * Referral to community resources or partners
             * Technical documentation and self-service guidance
           - Founders may negotiate scope, timeline, and deliverables
           - No guarantee of service approval, but all requests considered

       (f) PRIORITY CATEGORIES.
           The following receive priority consideration:
           
           (i)   Non-profit healthcare organizations
           (ii)  Public health departments and agencies
           (iii) Academic medical centers and research institutions
           (iv)  Community health centers serving underserved populations
           (v)   Healthcare initiatives in developing countries
           (vi)  Open-source healthcare projects
           (vii) Organizations responding to public health emergencies
           (viii)Small practices with <50 employees serving rural areas

       (g) COMMERCIAL ENTITIES.
           Commercial Entities and Healthcare Enterprises may also request
           free services under exceptional circumstances, including:
           
           (i)   Pilot programs with significant public health impact
           (ii)  Pro-bono work for charitable initiatives
           (iii) Emergency response or disaster relief scenarios
           (iv)  Collaboration on open-source contributions
           (v)   Research partnerships with data sharing agreements

       (h) TERMS OF FREE SERVICE DELIVERY.
           When founders provide free services:
           
           (i)   Services provided "as-is" with no warranty
           (ii)  Timeline and deliverables subject to founder availability
           (iii) Organization agrees to provide feedback and testimonial
           (iv)  Organization may be featured as case study (with approval)
           (v)   Organization encouraged to contribute back to community
           (vi)  Future paid engagement not required or expected

       (i) TRANSPARENCY AND FAIRNESS.
           - Aggregate statistics on requests and approvals published annually
           - Decision criteria and process remain transparent
           - Appeals can be submitted for denied requests
           - No discrimination based on geography, size, or sector

       (j) NO OBLIGATION.
           This provision does NOT create:
           
           (i)   Legal obligation for founders to provide services
           (ii)  Guarantee of approval for any request
           (iii) Enforceable right to free services
           (iv)  Liability for declined or delayed requests
           
           This is a voluntary program to support the community.

       (k) CONTACT FOR SERVICE REQUESTS.
           Submit service requests to: founders@openhims.org
           
           Include in your request:
           - Organization name and mission
           - Description of OpenHIMS use case
           - Specific services needed
           - Timeline and urgency
           - Community benefit explanation
           - Funding situation and constraints
           - Any supporting documentation

